<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="367" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,152,323]" pageId="9" pageNumber="367">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,468,152,179]" pageId="9" pageNumber="367">Differential Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Among Ecuadorian species, recognized by the combination of large body size (6.00 mm long), the elongate elytra, the dull grey dorsum with numerous microsetae, the small and rather sparse pronotal punctuation, and the large male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[620,688,224,250]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1769,1794]" captionTargetBox="[196,1420,368,1722]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1435,344,1744]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 6. Hydrochus maximus n. sp., habitus and male genitalia of holotype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3889420" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3889420/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="367">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
; described below). This is the largest known species of Ecuadorian 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1817" box="[151,273,260,286]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrochidae" genus="Hydrochus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="367" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,273,260,286]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="367">Hydrochus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; the elytra are elongate, whereas the relative sizes of the head and pronotum are similar to that of other species (pronotum length/head width = 0.96).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3889420" ID-Zenodo-Dep="3889420" box="[151,959,1769,1794]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3889420/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="367" startId="9.[151,250,1769,1794]" targetBox="[196,1420,368,1722]" targetPageId="9">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,959,1769,1794]" box="[151,959,1769,1794]" pageId="9" pageNumber="367">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,275,1769,1794]" pageId="9" pageNumber="367">FIGURE 6.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Perkins, 2020" authorityName="Perkins" authorityYear="2020" box="[281,488,1770,1794]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrochidae" genus="Hydrochus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="367" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maximus" status="n. sp.">
